ppur Taylor  Membership in this organization requires a student to be in the upper 10  of their class when considering all academic work  The Beta Gamma Sigma honor society sponsored a visit by Mr  Bruce Hazelgrove   83  the Vice President of Corporate Resources for New Market Corporation  the parent company to Afton Chemical Corporation and Ethyl Corporation  First classmen attended the roundtable discussion with Mr  Hazelgrove  The honor society also organized a field trip to Richmond  On the excursion  the group visited Virginia Commonwealth University to learn about graduate school opportunities  and met with the marketing staff of the Richmond Flying Squirrels minor league baseball team  ODE continues to produce the ECBU Online Journal which presents a sampling of the top student writing  This year s Best Paper award was given to Cadet William Truscott for his paper  The Jones Act and Its Effect on International Trade  Spring 2011 Newsletter  Field Test  Faculty Research  TAPS  New Faculty  Lopez Chair  Alumni in the News  Cadet Investment Group  Cadet Internships  BGS   ODE Activity  Cadet Awards  Alumni Survey  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 